<BLOCK4><TI>Sale of the Biomerge Tax Attributes</TI>
<P><P1>jj) Biomerge, during its second quarter of 2008, and at the request of New Nexia, repaid $100,000 of the demand loan.</P1>
<P1>kk) In November 2008, the Total Trust was shopping around for a &ldquo;Lossco&rdquo; to facilitate a conversion and sought proposals to undergo a transaction for the purpose of accessing the tax pools of the Lossco.</P1>
<P1>ll) On December 4, 2008, Cormark Securities Inc. gave a presentation to the Total Trust regarding the conversion to a corporation through a tax loss corporation.</P1>
<P1>mm) In the presentation, Cormark specifically identified Biomerge as a tax loss company that was prepared to enter into such a transaction.</P1>
<P1>nn) On or about February 2, 2009, the Total Trust sent a letter of intent to Biomerge and New Nexia proposing a transaction. In particular, the Total Trust proposed a transaction wherein Biomerge and New Nexia would receive consideration of $3,900,000 provided the available tax losses of Biomerge were not less than $70 million.</P1>
<P1>oo) Biomerge and New Nexia acknowledged and accepted the terms of the letter of intent on February 3, 2009.</P1></P></BLOCK4>
<BLOCK4><TI>Arrangement Agreement</TI>
<P><P1>pp) The Total Trust and Biomerge entered into an arrangement agreement on March 19, 2009 to, among other things, convert from an income trust to a corporation, by way of an arrangement (<BOLD>Arrangement Agreement</BOLD> and <BOLD>Arrangement</BOLD>, respectively) pursuant to Section 193 of the <EM>Business Corporations Act (Alberta)</EM>.</P1>
<P1>qq) The Total Trust and Biomerge set out, in the Arrangement Agreement, the transactions for the Arrangement as specified in a plan of arrangement (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Plan of Arrangement</BOLD>&rdquo;).</P1>
<P1>rr) Under the Plan of Arrangement the following events were to occur on the effective date of the Arrangement and be deemed to occur in the following order:
<P2>i) the Deed of Trust of the Total Trust was amended to (i) enable the trust units to be transferred to Bio merge, and (ii) facilitate the Arrangement and the implementation of the steps and transactions contemplated;</P2>
<P2>ii) the articles of continuance of Biomerge were amended to provide for the creation of a new class of shares of Biomerge (the &ldquo;<BOLD>New Total Common Shares</BOLD>&rdquo;);</P2>
<P2>iii) the Total Trust deposited with Bennett Jones LLP, in trust, $1,271,401 equal to the Biomerge Liabilities (as defined in the Plan of Arrangement) and Biomerge issued to the Total Trust a demand promissory note in the same amount;</P2>
<P2>iv) the 29,050,000 outstanding units of the Total Trust were transferred to Biomerge in exchange for 29,050,000 New Total Common Shares;</P2>
<P2>v) the 248,941,152 outstanding Biomerge voting common shares were transferred to Biomerge for cancellation in exchange for: (i) 56,730 New Total Common Shares and (ii) $702,293 cash consideration;</P2>
<P2>vi) the 435,647,055 outstanding Biomerge non-voting shares were transferred to Biomerge in exchange for cash consideration of $1,695,185;</P2>
<P2>vii) Biomerge changed its name to Total Energy Services Inc. (&ldquo;<BOLD>New Total</BOLD>&rdquo;);</P2>
<P2>viii) the Articles of Continuance of Biomerge were amended to reflect the foregoing and that the share capital of New Total would consist solely of the New Total Common Shares and the New Total Preferred Shares;</P2>
<P2>ix) the by-laws of TESL became the by-laws of New Total;</P2>
<P2>x) the Directors of TESL replaced the existing Directors of Biomerge and became the directors of New Total; and</P2>
<P2>xi) the Officers of TESL replaced the existing Officers of Biomerge and became the officers of New Total.</P2></P1>
<P1>ss) On or about May 20, 2009, the Total Trust changed the interest rate that was charged on certain notes owing from TESL (collectively, the &ldquo;<BOLD>Trust Debenture</BOLD>&rdquo;) with principal value of $213,469,860 from 2% to 15%. The Trust Debenture was unsecured, payable on demand and bore the following rates of interest (in respect of the period noted):
