<BLOCK1><TI><UNDER>AMENDED</UNDER> NOTICE OF MOTION</TI>
<P><BOLD>TAKE NOTICE THAT</BOLD> the Respondent will make a motion to the Court <UNDER>on Monday, October 16, 2017 at 2:00 p.m., or as soon after that time as the motion may be heard at the Tax Court of Canada, 701 West Georgia Street, 6th Floor, Vancouver, British Columbia</UNDER> <STRIKE>by teleconference on a date and time to be determined-by-the-Court</STRIKE>.</P>
<P><BOLD>THE MOTION IS FOR</BOLD> an order:</P>
<P>1. directing the appellant to respond to the Crown's follow-up questions dated March 31, 2017;</P>
<P>2. extending the time for communicating with the hearings coordinator as provided in the Court's order dated March 8, 2017; and</P>
<P>3. providing such further and other relief as this Court deems just.</P>
<P><BOLD>THE GROUNDS FOR THE MOTION ARE</BOLD> that:</P>
<P>1. This motion is brought by the Crown as directed by the Court's letter of May 25, 2017. The relevant background and circumstances are as follows.</P>
<P>2. The parties conducted oral examinations for discovery on October 17 and 18, 2016 in Calgary, Alberta.</P>
<P>3. By Order dated November 3, 2016, and by agreement, the parties were directed to satisfy undertakings given at the examinations for discovery by January 16, 2017 and to communicate with the hearings coordinator on or before February 16, 2017.</P>
<P>4. The appellant applied, by application dated January 12, 2017, for an amendment to the order dated November 3, 2016. As a result of the application, and by order dated January 16, 2017, the time for answering undertakings given at the examination for discovery was extended to January 31, 2017 and the parties were directed to communicate with the hearings coordinator by March 3, 2017.</P>
<P>5. The parties provided responses to undertakings and matters taken under advisement by letters dated January 31, 2017.</P>
<P>6. The appellant required the Crown's nominee to re-attend for an oral follow-up examination in Calgary respecting the Crown's responses to the appellant's undertaking requests and matters taken under advisement. The oral examination was subsequently held in Calgary on March 3, 2017.</P>
<P>7. By letter dated March 3, 2017, and with the agreement of the Crown, counsel for the appellant advised the Court that the parties anticipated the Crown would be (i) providing follow-up questions (to the appellant's nominee) by the end of March 2017 and (ii) answering undertakings given at the follow-up examination (held on March 3, 2017) by the end of March. Counsel for the appellant also asked that the parties further communicate with the hearings coordinator on or before April 15, 2017 to advise the Court of the status of the proceedings.</P>
<P>8. By order dated March 8, 2017, the order dated January 16, 2017 was amended to provide that (i) further written examinations for discovery questions and examinations for discovery shall be served on the opposing party by March 31, 2017; (ii) the answers to the further written examinations for discovery questions shall be served on the opposing party by March 31, 2017; and (iii) the parties shall communicate with the hearings coordinator in writing on or before April 15, 2017.</P>
<P>9. By letter dated March 30, 2017, counsel for the Crown delivered the Crown's responses arising from the appellant's oral follow-up examination for discovery of the Crown's nominee held on March 3, 2017.</P>
<P>10. By letter dated March 31, 2017, counsel for the Crown served follow-up questions in writing.</P>
<P>11. April 15, 2017 was a Saturday. The date for communicating with the hearings coordinator was diarized to April 17, 2017 (i.e., the Easter Monday holiday) in the Department of Justice calendar system for recording deadlines to counsels' calendars. On or about April 21, 2017, counsel for the Crown realized that neither party had communicated with the hearings coordinator. Counsel for the Crown thereafter wrote to the Court by letter dated April 21, 2017 and advised, in part, that the Crown was awaiting the appellant's responses to follow-up questions.</P>
<P>12. To date, the appellant has not responded to the Crown's follow-up questions.</P>
<P>13. In the circumstances, the appellant should be directed to provide answers to the Crown's follow-up questions and it would be just and reasonable to extend the date for the parties to communicate with the hearings coordinator.</P>
<P><BOLD>THE FOLLOWING DOCUMENTARY EVIDENCE</BOLD> will be used at the hearing of the motion:</P>
<P>1. the affidavit of Ruby Manget <UNDER>sworn and filed electronically on May 30, 2017</UNDER> <STRIKE>(to be filed)</STRIKE>; and</P>
<P>2. such further and other material as counsel may advise.</P>
<P><BOLD>THE ESTIMATED DURATION</BOLD> of this hearing will be 1/2 hour.</P>
