<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT OF RUBY MANGET</TI>
<P>I, Ruby Manget, of the City of Vancouver, in the Province of British Columbia, MAKE OATH AND SAY AS FOLLOWS:</P>
<P>1. I am employed as a legal assistant, in the Tax Law Services Section of the Department of Justice in Vancouver, British Columbia, and as such have personal knowledge of the matters to which I depose, except what is stated to be based on information and belief and, where so stated, I believe it to be true.</P>
<P>2. Perry Derksen, Robert Carvalho and Neva Beckie are the Department of Justice lawyers representing the Crown in this appeal. I am Mr. Derksen's legal assistant. Mr. Derksen has informed me of, and I believe, the facts stated in the following paragraphs of this affidavit.</P>
<P>3. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo; is a copy of the Court's letter dated May 25, 2017 directing that a motion and supporting affidavit be filed and served forthwith.</P>
<P>4. The parties conducted oral examinations for discovery on October 17 and 18, 2016 in Calgary, Alberta.</P>
<P>5. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo; is a copy of the Court's order dated November 3, 2016.</P>
<P>6. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo; is a copy of the Court's order dated January 16, 2017.</P>
<P>7. The parties provided responses to undertakings and matters taken under advisement by letters dated January 31, 2017.</P>
<P>8. The appellant required the Crown's nominee to re-attend for an oral follow-up examination in Calgary respecting the Crown's responses to the appellant's undertaking requests and matters taken under advisement. The oral examination was subsequently held in Calgary on March 3, 2017.</P>
<P>9. Counsel for the appellant wrote to the Court by letter dated March 3, 2017, a copy of which is attached as Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo;.</P>
<P>10. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;E&rdquo; is a copy of the Court's order dated March 8, 2017.</P>
<P>11. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;F&rdquo; is a copy of Mr. Derksen's letter to counsel for the appellant dated March 30, 2017 enclosing the Crown's responses arising from the appellant's follow-up examination for discovery held on March 3, 2017.</P>
<P>12. Attached is. Exhibit &ldquo;G&rdquo; is a copy of Mr. Derksen's letter to counsel for the appellant dated March 31, 2017 enclosing the Crown's follow-up questions arising from the examination for discovery of the appellant's nominee.</P>
<P>13. I diarized the deadlines established by the Court's order dated March 8, 2017 in the Department of Justice calendar system for recording deadlines to counsels' calendars. In particular, I diarized the deadline for communicating with the hearings coordinator as Monday, April 17, 2017 because April 15, 2017 fell on a Saturday. I did not realize at the time that April 17, 2017 was Easter Monday, a holiday.</P>
<P>14. On or about April 21, 2017, Mr. Derksen realized that neither party had communicated with the hearings coordinator.</P>
<P>15. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;H&rdquo; is a copy of Mr. Derksen's letter to the Court dated April 21, 2017.</P>
<P>16. To date, the appellant has not responded to the Crown's follow-up questions served on March 31, 2017.</P>
