<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II">AFFIDAVIT OF ROSALIND SEMCHUK (RE: APPELLANT'S MOTION)</TI>
<P>I, Rosalind Semchuk, Legal Assistant, of the City of Calgary, in the Province of Alberta, MAKE OATH AND SAY THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am employed as a legal assistant with the law firm of Fasken Martineau DuMoulin LLP in Calgary, Alberta and as such have personal knowledge of the matters to which I depose, except where stated to be based on information on belief and whereso stated I believe it to be true.</P>
<P>2. This affidavit is being filed in support of the Appellant's Notice of Motion dated July 14, 2017 related to refusals to answer questions at examinations for discovery.</P>
<P>3. Curtis R. Stewart is the lawyer representing the Appellant in this appeal. I am Mr. Stewart's legal assistant. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of the transcript of the examination for discovery of the Respondent's nominee, Mr. Hercules Karasavidis, held on October 18, 2016 (the &ldquo;Original Transcript&rdquo;) and an index setting out exhibits, objections taken and requests associated with the examination (the &ldquo;Original Index&rdquo;).</P>
<P>4. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;A-1&rdquo; is a true copy of the document marked as Exhibit A-4 at the examination for discovery of Hercules Karasavidis held on October 18, 2016.</P>
<P>5. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a copy of the Respondent's Answers to Undertakings and Matters Taken Under Advisement, which was provided by Respondent's counsel in the original of the attached copy of a letter dated January 31, 2017.</P>
<P>6. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a copy of the Respondent's Revised Answers to Undertakings and Matters Taken Under Advisement, which was provided by Respondent's counsel in the original of the attached email dated February 28, 2017.</P>
<P>7. Attached as &ldquo;Exhibit D&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of the transcript of the further examination for discovery of the Respondent's nominee, Mr. Hercules Karasavidis, held on March 3, 2017 (the &ldquo;Further Transcript&rdquo;) and an index setting out exhibits, objections taken and requests associated with the examination (the &ldquo;Further Index&rdquo;).</P>
<P>8. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;E&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of the Respondent's Answers to Further Undertakings and Matters Taken Under Advisement which was provided by Respondent's counsel in the original of the attached copy of a letter dated March 30, 2017.</P>
