<BLOCK1><TI><UNDER>ORDER</UNDER></TI>
<P>WHEREAS the Respondent filed an Amended Notice of Motion on July 18, 2017, seeking an order:
<P1>1. directing the Appellant to respond to the Crown's follow-up questions dated March 31, 2017;</P1>
<P1>2. extending the time for communicating with the Hearings Coordinator as provided for in this Court's Order dated March 8, 2017; and</P1>
<P1>3. providing such further and other relief as this Court deems just;</P1></P>
<P>AND WHEREAS the Appellant filed a Motion on August 16, 2017, seeking an order requiring the Respondent to, <EM>interalia</EM>, answer questions and produce unredacted copies of documents related thereto;</P>
<P>AND WHEREAS both the Respondent's and Appellant's Motion were heard on October 16, 2017;</P>
<P>AND WHEREAS UPON hearing from both parties the Court reserved its decision in respect of the Appellant's Motion;</P>
<P>IT IS ORDERED THAT:
<P1>a) the Respondent's Motion is allowed;</P1>
<P1>b) by December 15, 2017, the Appellant shall provide answers to the Respondent's follow-up questions dated March 31, 2017; and</P1>
<P1>c) within 60 days from the date of the issuance of the Court's decision in the Appellant's Motion, the parties shall report to the Court with respect to the status of the remaining pre-trial steps in this Appeal, together with a timeline for the completion thereof.</P1></P>
<P>Signed at Toronto, Canada, this 2nd day of November 2017.</P>
<P><UNDER>&ldquo;Henry A. Visser&rdquo;</UNDER></P>
<P>Visser J.</P></BLOCK1>
